  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Live saving cash assistance in border area Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The most vulnerable households will be selected, with a division of 360 IDP and 40 host community hhs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed intervention is a response to the food crisis in the border area with Niger and Mali in Burkina Faso due to influx of internally displaced people (IDP). A large group of IDP&#x2019;s are hosted by 3 local communities that are already struggling with a degrading food and nutrition situation. Cordaid will work via OCADES to distribute cash. The cash support will save lives.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide 400 families (360 IDP, 40 host communities) with lifesaving food security support in Titao communities</narrative>
  </description>
